1. What is the purpose of a breakpoint?

The purpose of a breakpoint is to tell the debugger tool in which line I want to start debugging.

2. Does the line of code on a breakpoint run when you start debugging?
No, it's stops before the line get executed.

3. How do we debug the next line of code?
Clicking on the down arrow symbol "Step over".

4. What does the step into command do?
Goes to the first line of the method called in the current line.

5. What is the difference between evaluate expression and evaluate code fragment?
When you evaluate an expression that evaluate a single line of code without semicolon and when you evaluate a code fragment you takes several lines of codes using semicolon at the end of every line. 
